Arboran Commonwealth

The Arboran Commonwealth is a territory of architectural wonder on the planet Miravalis, and a story of perseverance and ecological resilience. Long ago, the people of the region lived in the thick woodland forests that cover this area, until about the mid 400s. Around this time, an inexplicable surge of wild magic spanned the world, and this surge ripped open tears in planar reality in the region of the Arboran.

All throughout the immense forests, fiends and aberrations began spawning, entering from rifts to the Nine Hells, Underdark, and Shadowfell. Threatened and swarmed by these monsters, the people of the Arboran refused to leave their region behind. So instead of running, or seeking refuge, they simply climbed. Many weeks and months of extreme vigilance passed, and the people of the Arboran had established a system of tree houses. Since then, the Arboran continue to live amongst branches, hundreds of feet in the air.

Furthermore, the technology of this region is the most advanced of the planet, second to Morellus. Living against common sense required practical use of mechanical engineering, as well as the use of ancient Elvish magic. After protecting Elvish mystics for years from attacks from the very few airborne monsters, a Mythal was placed over the region, completely masking its presence from anyone unknowing of the commonwealth.
